The paper discusses a framework for question answering over knowledge graphs, which involves natural language processing and optimization techniques. This falls under the scope of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The framework also involves working with a knowledge graph, which is a type of database (cs.DB). Additionally, the system uses connection density between entity and relation candidates, which is a measure of similarity or relevance, and this falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
